      <!-- Monthly Recap -->
      <mj-wrapper padding="0 0 15">
        <mj-section padding="10 0" background-color="#fff" border-radius="3">
          <mj-column>
            <mj-text align="left" font-size="20" color="#4A4A4A" font-weight="700" padding-bottom="0">Monthly Recap</mj-text>

            <mj-text align="left" font-size="14" color="#4A4A4A" font-weight="400" padding-top="0" padding-bottom="0">
              <p>This past month, five Our Revolution candidates won their primaries, and in Kansas City, the residents voted decisively in support of a $15 per hour bill, in spite of their state legislators' efforts to prevent a rise in the minimum wage. Additionally, local groups lobbied their Representatives to support the #PeoplesPlatform, Senator Bernie Sanders introduced the Medicare for all Act of 2017, Our Revolution launched a new membership package, and the fight for SB 562, which would bring healthcare to all Californians, continues. <strong>Read on to find out more!</strong></p>
            </mj-text>
          </mj-column>
        </mj-section>
      </mj-wrapper>

      <mj-wrapper background-color="#f5f5f5" padding="0 0 15">
        <mj-section background-color="#fff" padding="10 0 0" border-radius="3">
          <mj-column>
            <mj-text align="left" font-size="16" color="#4A4A4A" font-weight="700">Notable Victories</mj-text>

            <mj-text padding-top="0" font-size="14">
              <ul>
                <li><strong>Randall Woodfin</strong> - Won Municipal Election, Runoff Election Oct. 3, 2017</li>
                <li><strong>Paul Feeney</strong> - Won Primary, General Election Oct. 17, 2017</li>
                <li><strong>Garlin Gilchrist</strong> - Won Primary, General Election Nov. 7, 2017 </li>
                <li><strong>Rich Updegrove</strong> - Won Primary, General Election Nov. 7, 2017</li>
                <li><strong>Jasmin Santana</strong> - Won Primary, General Election Nov. 7, 2017</li>
                <li><strong>Carlos Menchaca</strong> - Won Primary, General Election Nov. 7, 2017</li>
                <li><strong>Gina Perez</strong> - Elected to Ames County School Board</li>
                <li><strong>Kansas City for $15</strong> - Passed</li>
              </ul>
            </mj-text>

            <mj-image src="https://s.bsd.net/ourrev/main/page/-/images/newsletter/s4p.png" padding="15 0 0 0"></mj-image>
            <mj-text font-size="14">
              <h3>Summer for Progress</h3>
              <p>Our Revolution and partner organizations called on progressives to fight for the #PeoplesPlatform - eight bills currently in the House of Representatives that will address the concerns of everyday Americans. Groups and members across the country met recently with their Representatives in Congress and delivered a petition with signatures from constituents in each district who support the platform. More than 100 congressional visits and thousands of phone calls later, we moved members of congress on all 8 bills, gaining more than 60 co-sponsors. The fight is just getting started! Expect to hear more about the #PeoplesPlatform in the coming months.</p>

              <h3>Medicare for All</h3>
              <p>Senator Bernie Sanders introduced the Medicare for all Act of 2017, which already has 16 cosponsors. “Sen. Sanders' Medicare for All bill makes health care a right, not a privilege. Right now, 28 million people do not have health insurance and tens of millions are uninsured,” said Our Revolution President Nina Turner. “Providing safe and accessible healthcare is a moral imperative for our country. Our Revolution will be pushing our members to action, asking their senators to cosponsor and vote for Sen. Sanders’ bill.” Stay tuned on this front! While we can’t promise this will will be the law of the land in 2017, or even before 2021, we must press ahead to grow the movement around Medicare for All.</p>
            </mj-text>

            <mj-image src="https://s.bsd.net/ourrev/main/page/-/membership.jpg" padding="0"></mj-image>

            <mj-text font-size="14" padding-bottom="25">
              <h3>Membership</h3>
              <p>This month, Senator Nina Turner, President of Our Revolution, sent an email outlining our new membership package. If you missed it, <a href="https://go.ourrevolution.com/page/s/membership-package?source=em170925" target="_blank">complete this form &raquo</a> to receive your free membership package that includes:</p>

              <ul>
                <li>An Our Revolution membership card</li>
                <li>A welcome packet from Senator Turner and staff</li>
                <li>A free Our Revolution sticker</li>
                <li>Access to this monthly membership newsletter</li>
                <li>Connecting you with a local Our Revolution group or status as a “Member-at-Large”</li>
                <li>Having your voice heard in surveys which will shape the future of OR</li>
              </ul>
            </mj-text>
          </mj-column>
